text:
Laudo Natel (14 September 1920 – 18 May 2020) was a Brazilian politician. He was born in São Manuel, São Paulo. He was a member of the National Renewal Alliance. He was Vice Governor of São Paulo from 1963 to 1966 and Governor from 1966 to 1967 and again from 1971 to 1975.
Natel died on 18 May 2020 at his home in São Paulo at the age of 99.
